<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="535" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1014,1975]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1014,1039]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Posterior cercus with acuminate apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[890,990,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[944,990,1014,1039]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="163.0">163</number>
</figureCitation>
); without dorsal projections (
<figureCitation box="[1322,1418,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[1375,1418,1014,1039]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="164.0">164</number>
</figureCitation>
); hypoproct bacilliform in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[587,687,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[641,687,1050,1075]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="163.0">163</number>
</figureCitation>
); phallus with narrow base, wider mostly, with a dorsal subapical narrow appendix in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[522,618,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[575,618,1086,1111]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="167.0">167</number>
</figureCitation>
) and subapical spines laterally best visualized in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1325,1423,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[1377,1423,1086,1111]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="168.0">168</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="535" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1014,1975]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1122,1147]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[360,421,1122,1147]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[444,550,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[505,550,1122,1147]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="161.0">161</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[579,643,1122,1147]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">Head</emphasis>
: Face slightly divergent toward the proboscis, brown, with gray pruinescence visible in ventral view, about 
<date box="[643,677,1159,1183]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
<number box="[643,655,1159,1183]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="3.0">3</number>
X
</date>
longer than lower width. Ocellar tubercle protuberant, brown with brown pruinescence; ocelli light brown. Scape and pedicel yellow with black bristles, postpedicel with yellow base and brown apex with small yellow bristles, about 
<number box="[761,795,1230,1255]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X longer than pedicel; stylus about 
<number box="[1234,1269,1230,1255]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="2.5">2.5</number>
X longer than postpedicel. Proboscis yellow, slightly longer than head height. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[894,983,1266,1291]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">Thorax</emphasis>
yellow, shiny (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1267,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[1221,1267,1266,1291]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="161.0">161</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs yellow, except for hind femur and tibia with brown apical ring and all tarsomeres 
<number box="[978,1020,1302,1327]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
black; hind tibia and tarsus posterior with anterodorsal and posterodorsal rows of longer bristles. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[885,950,1338,1363]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[973,1076,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[1033,1076,1338,1363]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="162.0">162</number>
</figureCitation>
) hyaline, pterostigma, brown, conspicuous, about 
<number box="[374,409,1375,1399]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="2.9">2.9</number>
X longer than wide. Halter yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,926,1374,1399]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">Abdomen</emphasis>
yellow, shiny (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1199,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[1154,1199,1374,1399]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="161.0">161</number>
</figureCitation>
); tergite 
<number box="[1300,1314,1375,1399]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="8.0">8</number>
divided in two subrectangular plates; sternite 
<number box="[565,579,1411,1435]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="8.0">8</number>
divided in two subrectangular plates. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1042,1173,1410,1435]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">Terminalia</emphasis>
: Anterior cercus with proclinate dorsal projection in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[661,762,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[717,762,1446,1471]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="163.0">163</number>
</figureCitation>
), with posterior margin with a small median projection in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[310,415,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[369,415,1482,1507]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="164.0">164</number>
</figureCitation>
); descendant plate subrectangular in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[1054,1159,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[1113,1159,1482,1507]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="165.0">165</number>
</figureCitation>
). Posterior cercus with acuminate apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[517,617,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[571,617,1518,1543]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="163.0">163</number>
</figureCitation>
); without dorsal projections (
<figureCitation box="[952,1049,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[1006,1049,1518,1543]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="164.0">164</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct bacilliform in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[221,316,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[273,316,1554,1579]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="163.0">163</number>
</figureCitation>
) and comma-shaped in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[760,858,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[812,858,1554,1579]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="165.0">165</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrial ventral lobe rounded at apex; spiniform bristles mesially and longer bristles apically (
<figureCitation box="[680,782,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
