<figureCitation box="[403,508,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[463,508,1626,1651]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="169.0">169</number>
</figureCitation>
), without long bristles. Phallus with narrow base, wider mostly, longer than hypandrium, with a dorsal subapical narrow appendix in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[941,1037,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[994,1037,1662,1687]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="167.0">167</number>
</figureCitation>
) and subapical spines laterally best visualized in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[472,575,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
Fig. 
<number box="[529,575,1698,1723]" pageId="33" pageNumber="535" value="168.0">168</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite wider than long, U-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1180,1283,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
