</figureCitation>
). Bacilliform sclerite without folds and longer than subepandrial sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[820,918,1734,1759]" captionStart="FIGURES 161 – 169" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 161 – 169. Opeatocerata spinipenis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 161. habitus, lateral view; 162. wing; 163. terminalia, lateral view; 164. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 165. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 166. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 167. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 168. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view; 169. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252540/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="535">
